  <title>Led Blinking </title>
<subsection xml:id="subsec-Introduction-led">
  <title>Introduction</title>
  <p>This experiment guides the learners to blink a 5mm LED, a simple experiment to test the software and hardware components to verify whether installation procedures are correct. This experiment acts as a visual indicator for many applications such as street light, dancing LED and so on. The output of this experiment can be physically seen. This establishes a solid foundation for learners to undertake complex problems in the future. This kind of concept is used in electronic devices like traffic lights. It acts as an indicator to know the state change when the current passes through it. Dancing LED in highways is one of the major applications, of turning on the LED. Dancing LED is a visual sign indicator in highways to prevent accidents between heavy load vehicles.</p>
  <image source="/images/LED_2.JPG" width="30%"/>
</subsection>
