    <p>Resistor is a passive two terminal electrical component which can be fixed in a hole. It is used to control the flow of the current, which divides the required voltage for each component. Behaviour of the resistor is based on Ohmâ€™s Law V=IR. </p>
    <p>There are different types of resistors, such as fixed resistor, variable resistor, thermistors and light dependent resistors that are used in industries.</p>
    <p>LED is a small diode that can handle only 5V of the current. Therefore, to avoid failure of the LED, resistors are used. Fig 2.1.2 shows the image of a simple resistor.</p>
