  <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-LED">
    <title>LED</title>
    <figure>
      <image source="/images/LED-circuit.jpg" width="40%"/>
      <caption>LED </caption>
    </figure>
    <p>LED stands for Light Emitting Diode which emits light when current passes through it and it is a semiconductor device that conducts an electrical property. LED has two legs, longer leg is called as anode (positive) and shorter leg is called as (negative) cathode. LED is smaller in size, easy to handle and the cost of the LED is cheap. LED can be used in remote control devices to work   in a short range of frequency fig 2.1.3; LED image is given for understanding purpose.</p>
