<subsection xml:id="subsec-Code">
  <title>Code</title>
  <program>
    void setup() { 
      LED=8; // initialize digital pin 8  as an output.
      pinMode(8, OUTPUT);//mode declaration for D8
      }
      // the loop function runs over and over again forever
      void loop() {
      digitalWrite(8, HIGH); // turn the LED on (HIGH is the voltage level)
      delay(1000); // wait for a second
      digitalWrite(8, LOW); // turn the LED off by making the voltage LOW
      delay(1000); // wait for a second
      }      
  </program>
  <term>Code Explanation </term>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Pin Mode function is used to configure a specific pin either for input or output purpose. 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        In void setup(), LED will be declared as output  pin 13 .
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        In void Loop, digitalwrite is () used to set the pin as high or low. For example, digital Write (13, HIGH). 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Pin 13 is to set to high. 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Delay is used to pause the program for a certain period of time.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Delay of 1000 micro second i.e. 1 second can be set 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Using (digital Write, LOW) function LED will turn off.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
